{"lemma": "مِجَنٌّ", "slug": "مِجَنٌّ", "root": "ج.ن.ن", "root_slug": "ج-ن-ن", "root_link": "/words/roots/ج-ن-ن", "pos": "N", "pos_camel": "noun", "paradigm": [], "frequency_in_corpus": 0, "cross_references": {"qac": {"found": false}, "wiktextract": {"found": true, "entry_count": 1, "pos_tags": ["noun"], "has_etymology": true, "sense_count": 1}, "lanes": {"found": true, "entry_ids": ["n6401"], "search_url": "https://lanelexicon.com/?s=%D9%85%D9%90%D8%AC%D9%8E%D9%86%D9%8C%D9%91"}}, "translations": {"en": "shield", "fa": "سپر", "ur": "ڈھال", "tr": "kalkan", "id": "perisai", "bn": "ঢাল", "es": "escudo", "fr": "bouclier", "de": "Schild", "ru": "щит", "zh": "盾牌"}, "definition": {"source": "wiktextract", "senses": [{"pos": "noun", "gloss": "a shield", "examples": [{"text": "لَمْ تُقْطَعْ يَدُ سَارِقٍ فِي عَهْدِ رَسُولِ اللَّٰهِ —صَلَّى اللَّٰهُ عَلَيْهِ وَسَلَّمَ— فِي أَقَلَّ مِنْ ثَمَنِ الْمِجَنِّ حَجَفَةٍ أَوْ تُرْسٍ وَكِلَاهُمَا ذُو ثَمَنٍ.", "english": "During the lifetime of Allah’s Messenger (ﷺ), the hand of a thief was not cut off for less than the price of a shield, skin-shield or scutum, and both of them are valuable."}]}]}, "etymology": {"source": "wiktextract", "text": "Tool noun from the root ج ن ن (j n n). Cognate to Classical Syriac ܡܓܶܢܳܐ (məgennā, “shield”), Phoenician 𐤌𐤂𐤍 (mgn, “shield”), and Hebrew מָגֵן (māgén, “shield”)."}, "ipa": ["/mi.d͡ʒann/"], "lanes_definition": {"source": "lanes", "entries": [{"entry_id": "n6401", "headword_ar": "مِجَنٌّ", "root": "jn", "body": [{"kind": "italic_en", "text": "A shield;"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "(S, Mgh, Msb, K;) because the owner conceals, or protects, himself with it; (Mgh, Msb;) as also ↓"}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "mijan~apN", "text_ar": "مِجَنَّةٌ", "orth_type": "arrow"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "(Lh, K) and ↓"}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "junaAnN", "text_ar": "جُنَانٌ", "orth_type": "arrow"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "and ↓"}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "junaAnapN", "text_ar": "جُنَانَةٌ", "